intermittently and sold small amount of dollars to halt a new upswing, but the amount of selling was unknown. The central bank does not comment on its monetary actions. `` For a while, the dollar is unlikely to rise back much, because the <ORGANIZATION> G-7 </ORGANIZATION> central banks will coordinate intervention actively,'' Ms. <PERSON> Takeuchi </PERSON> added. On the stock exchange, `` The Nikkei seems to have entered its uptrend finally,'' said <PERSON> Masahiro </PERSON> <PERSON> Umemori </PERSON>, a stock analyst with <ORGANIZATION> Nomura </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Securities </ORGANIZATION>. He attributed the index's consistent rise to the yen's rebound against the dollar following the <ORGANIZATION> G-7 </ORGANIZATION> monetary talks.
