<HEAD>Rain in Northeast; Cold in North-Central U.S.</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
 Showers soaked parts of the Northeast today, causing authorities to warn of flooding in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Jersey </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Pennsylvania </LOCATION>, while a cold front in the north-central <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> dropped temperatures to near freezing. Scattered showers and thunderstorms dumped rain Monday from <LOCATION> Mississippi </LOCATION> to the southern half of the <LOCATION> Atlantic </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Coast </LOCATION>. One thunderstorm along the coast of <LOCATION> North </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Carolina </LOCATION> spawned a tornado near the town of Seaside. More than 2 -LCB- inches of rain fell at <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Bern </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> N.C. </LOCATION>, and more than 1 -LCB- inches fell at Cherry Point, <LOCATION> N.C </LOCATION>. The showers and thunderstorms spread to the <LOCATION> Northeast </LOCATION> early today. Small stream and urban flood watches were posted for much of southern <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Jersey </LOCATION> and east-central <LOCATION> Pennsylvania </LOCATION>, where up to 3 inches of rain were possible. Clouds and rain kept temperatures in the 50s and 60s over much of the Southeast on Monday. Strong northwesterly winds ushered more cold air into the central part of the country. A gale warning was in effect for <LOCATION> Lake </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Huron </LOCATION>, and frost and freeze advisories were posted overnight for northwest <LOCATION> Wisconsin </LOCATION>. Record high temperatures on Monday included <LOCATION> Pocatello </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Idaho </LOCATION>, which registered 89 degrees, and <LOCATION> Tucson </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Ariz. </LOCATION>, with 103 degrees. Reports at 2 a.m. EDT today included: EAST: <LOCATION> Albany </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> N.Y. </LOCATION>, 57 cloudy; <ORGANIZATION> Atlanta </ORGANIZATION> 56 drizzle; <ORGANIZATION> Boston </ORGANIZATION> 57 cloudy; <LOCATION> Charleston 