no bearing on whether the high court considers <LOCATION> Minnesota </LOCATION>'s challenge, <PERSON> Tunheim </PERSON> said. `` That case was not nearly as well-developed as the <LOCATION> Minnesota </LOCATION> case,'' <PERSON> Tunheim </PERSON> said. The 1st Circuit issued a one-sentence order affirming the law, while the decisions in the <LOCATION> Minnesota </LOCATION> case have prompted lengthy dissents, <PERSON> Tunheim </PERSON> said.
