<HEAD>Lawmen Guarding School Officials, Facilities</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HAZLEHURST, Miss. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Police are guarding public buildings following a week-long series of suspicious fires and telephone threats against schools and school officials. `` This might be related to our attempt to break up a drug pipeline at the school earlier this year,'' said School Superintendent <PERSON> George </PERSON> <PERSON> French </PERSON>. `` There was an attempt -LRB- by drug dealers -RRB- to get a foothold in it, and we've worked very hard to eliminate drugs,'' he said. French also speculated the fires could be reprisals against administrators for the expulsion of a gun-toting 14-year-old male student several weeks ago. `` We had a student expelled because he brought his father's gun to school with the intent to kill another student,'' he said. He declined to identify the minor. French said the student fired one shot that hit a portable classroom. `` The consensus is that the fires are all connected,'' said state chief deputy fire marshal <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Chamblee </PERSON> of <PERSON> Jackson </PERSON>. `` It's giving us indications that someone has a vendetta or a loose screw,'' he said of the investigation, adding that his office will post a $ 1,000 reward. Monday morning, someone pushed a burning wad of paper behind a ceiling tile at the county's temporary welfare office downtown. The fire did little damage and was being investigated as arson, said <LOCATION> Hazlehurst </LOCATION> Public Safety Director <PERSON> Thomas </PERSON> <PERSON> Quarles </PERSON>. Another fire early Sunday gutted a vacant building being rented by <PERSON> Woodrow </PERSON> <PERSON> Purcer </PERSON>, a candidate in a special election for supervisor, <PERSON> Quarles </PERSON> said. <PERSON> Quarles </PERSON> said the fire is believed to be also arson-related. <PERSON> Purcer </PERSON> said: `` It had nothing to do with the election; it just happened.'' Four fires set at <ORGANIZATION> Hazlehurst </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Elementary </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> School </ORGA