<HEAD>U.N., Namibian Officials in Accord on Election Law</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WINDHOEK, Namibia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> United </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Nations </ORGANIZATION> officials and <LOCATION> Namibia </LOCATION>'s administrator reached agreement Tuesday on the laws governing the territory's pre-independence elections in six weeks The elections, set for Nov. 7-11, will pave the way for independence in <LOCATION> Namibia </LOCATION>, which has been ruled by <LOCATION> South </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Africa </LOCATION> for 74 years. <LOCATION> Namibia </LOCATION>'s South African administrator <PERSON> Louis </PERSON> <PERSON> Pienaar </PERSON> and the head of the <ORGANIZATION> U.N. </ORGANIZATION> monitoring contingent, <PERSON> Martti </PERSON> <PERSON> Ahtisaari </PERSON>, finalized the election laws Tuesday, but will not release the details until later this week, <PERSON> Pienaar </PERSON>'s spokesman <PERSON> Gerhard </PERSON> <PERSON> Roux </PERSON> said. Ten parties and coalitions have qualified to contest the elections for a national assembly that will draw up <LOCATION> Namibia </LOCATION>'s constitution The favorite in the polls is the <ORGANIZATION> South-West </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Africa </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> People </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> 's </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Organization </ORGANIZATION>, a leftist-oriented independence movement that waged a 23-year war against South African rule Its main rival is expected to be the <ORGANIZATION> Democratic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Turnhalle </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Alliance </ORGANIZATION>, a moderate, multiracial coalition that favors a free-market economy. <LOCATION> South </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Africa </LOCATION> agreed to grant independence to <LOCATION> Namibia </LOCATION> last year under a regional peace accord that also calls for the phased withdrawal of 50,000 Cuban troops from <LOCATION> Angola </LOCATION>. No date for Namibian independence has been set, but it is expected to be early next year.
