<FIRST>a e BC-WKD--FilmReview Adv00   09-26 0564</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-WKD--Film Review, Adv 00,0571</SECOND>
<HEAD>$adv00</HEAD>
<HEAD>For Release Anytime</HEAD>
<HEAD>AP WEEKEND ENTERTAINMENT AND ARTS</HEAD>
<HEAD>At the Movies: ``A Dry White Season''</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By BOB THOMAS</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
 <PERSON> Marlon </PERSON> <PERSON> Brando </PERSON> returns to the screen in `` A Dry White Season'' after a lamentable nine-year absence. The not-so-good news is that he appears on the screen less than 10 minutes. Yes, he looks bulky, resembling <PERSON> Raymond </PERSON> <PERSON> Burr </PERSON> in his courtroom robe. Yes, he affects a British accent -LRB- how he loves props -RRB- that drew an initial titter from the preview audience. But no, the <PERSON> Brando </PERSON> magnetism has not diminished in his long layoff. He remains a dominating force. Like `` Cry Freedom'' and `` A World Apart,'' `` A Dry White Season'' was filmed in <LOCATION> Zimbabwe </LOCATION> and looks at <LOCATION> South </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Africa </LOCATION>'s apartheid from a white viewpoint The central figure is <PERSON> Donald </PERSON> <PERSON> Sutherland </PERSON>, a teacher at an exclusive white boy's school. He is vaguely unsettled by the signs of oppression all around him and by the tacit agreement with the government's policy by his family and fellow faculty members. Apartheid strikes close to <PERSON> Sutherland </PERSON> when his son's playmate and the boy's father are kidnapped, tortured and murdered by the Special Police. He enlists the help of the shadowy <PERSON> Zakes </PERSON> <PERSON> Mokae </PERSON>, a taxi driver with good connections; <PERSON> Susan </PERSON> <PERSON> Sarandon </PERSON>, a liberal reporter; and a noted defense lawyer, played by <PERSON> Brando </PERSON>. <PERSON> Sutherland </PERSON>'s efforts to seek justice are thwarted, and he loses his job, his wife, his standing in the white community and more. Even his own daughter betrays him. Only one element of hope remains: He has inculcated his young son with a sense of outrage at the vicious repression of the South African regime. The sure-handed direction of <ORGANIZATION> Euzhan </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Palcy </ORGANIZATION> -LRB- `` Sugar Cane Alley'' -RRB- and her talent for drawing the best fro