<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 How much you enjoy the 1982 comedy `` Baby It's You'' may depend on your appreciation of three alumni of <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Jersey </LOCATION>'s working class: <PERSON> Frank </PERSON> <PERSON> Sinatra </PERSON>, <PERSON> Bruce </PERSON> <PERSON> Springsteen </PERSON> and director <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Sayles </PERSON> The year is 1967 and <PERSON> Jill </PERSON> <PERSON> Rosen </PERSON> -LRB- <PERSON> Rosanna </PERSON> <PERSON> Arquette </PERSON> -RRB- is a senior at a <LOCATION> Trenton </LOCATION> high school, an aspiring actress from an upper-middle class family who seeks acceptance to <PERSON> Sarah </PERSON> <PERSON> Lawrence </PERSON> <PERSON> College </PERSON>. She catches the attention of <PERSON> Albert </PERSON> `` Sheik'' Capadilupo, the swaggering, sharply dressed garbage man's son who ranks `` <PERSON> Jesus </PERSON> <PERSON> Christ </PERSON>, <PERSON> Frank </PERSON> <PERSON> Sinatra </PERSON> and me'' as the most important people in his life. On the surface, another `` bad boy meets nice girl'' story. Sheik gets <PERSON> Jill </PERSON>, <PERSON> Sheik </PERSON> loses <PERSON> Jill </PERSON>, <PERSON> Sheik </PERSON> wins her back. But `` Baby It's You'' has much more to offer With humor and intelligence, <PERSON> Sayles </PERSON> touches on the conflicts of class and sex. What to do with choices, too many and too few. <PERSON> Sayles </PERSON> -LRB- `` Matewan,'' `` Eight Men Out'' -RRB- collaborated on the story with <PERSON> Amy </PERSON> <PERSON> Robinson </PERSON>, whose experiences were closer to <PERSON> Jill </PERSON>'s. `` Certainly I could relate to both of them,'' <PERSON> Sayles </PERSON> said in a recent phone interview. `` A lot of kids ended up in <LOCATION> Vietnam </LOCATION> or working in a factory or married with kids right out of high school. Your potential is cut off.'' Rock' n' roll, from the Trashmen to <LOCATION> Procul </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Harem </LOCATION>, is everywhere, but <PERSON> Sinatra