on in January 1988, is eager to own entertainment `` software'' such as movies and TV shows as a complement to the hardware such as VCRs and television sets it has been making for years. `` There are only a limited supply of companies like this,'' analyst <PERSON> Jeffrey </PERSON> <PERSON> Logsdon </PERSON> said of <LOCATION> Columbia </LOCATION>. He follows the entertainment business for the investment firm <ORGANIZATION> Crowell </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Weedon </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> ; </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Los </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Angeles </LOCATION>. <ORGANIZATION> Columbia </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Pictures </ORGANIZATION> operates two movie studios, <ORGANIZATION> Columbia </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Pictures </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> Tri-Star </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Pictures </ORGANIZATION>, and has a library of more than 2,700 film titles and more than 260 TV series. Recent movie releases from <LOCATION> Columbia </LOCATION> have included `` Ghostbusters II,'' `` The Karate Kid Part III,'' and `` When <PERSON> Harry </PERSON> <PERSON> Met </PERSON> <PERSON> Sally </PERSON> ...'' while Tri-Star has come out with `` See No Evil, Hear No Evil'' and `` Lock Up.'' <ORGANIZATION> Columbia </ORGANIZATION> is one of the leading suppliers of TV programming through its <ORGANIZATION> Columbia </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Pictures </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Television </ORGANIZATION> and <PERSON> Merv </PERSON> <PERSON> Griffin </PERSON> Enterprises units. <LOCATION> Columbia </LOCATION> produces or distributes 11 TV series that are being aired in prime time, including `` Who's The Boss,'' `` Designing Women'' and `` Married ... with Children.'' <ORGANIZATION> Columbia </ORGANIZATION> also owns <PERSON> Merv </PERSON> <PERSON> Griffin </PERSON> <PERSON> Enterprises </PERSON>, whose shows include `` Wheel of Fortune'