<SECOND>PM-Wall Street 2pm,0315</SECOND>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Stock prices were broadly higher in relatively light afternoon trading led by big institutional investors and computerized program strategies. The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials was up 18.05 points to 2,677.24 at 2 p.m. EDT. The blue-chip indicator was up 15.39 points at noon but below earlier highs. On Monday, the average fell 22.42 points on a broad-based sell-off. Advancing issues outpaced decliners by a margin of about 8 to 5 on the <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION>, with 824 issues up, 498 down and 541 unchanged. Volume on the <ORGANIZATION> Big </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Board </ORGANIZATION> came to 104.32 million shares. The stock market got a boost early in the day from a government report that showed surprising strength in new factory orders for durable goods. The <ORGANIZATION> Commerce </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> reported that factory orders for `` big ticket'' durable items such as cars, airplanes and machinery, rose 3.8 percent in August, the biggest advance this year. The market had expected a slight decline. Despite the overall strength in today's market, Wall Street analysts said it still lacked strong leadership. `` There's no firm conviction,'' said <PERSON> Emmanuel </PERSON> <PERSON> Geronimous </PERSON>. `` The market could swing either way.'' The <ORGANIZATION> NYSE </ORGANIZATION>'s composite index of all its listed common stocks was up 1.04 to 192.32. On the <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION>, the market value index was 1.46 higher at 382.86. Among actively traded issues on the <ORGANIZATION> NYSE </ORGANIZATION>, <ORGANIZATION> Columbia </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Pictures </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Entertainment </ORGANIZATION> was down \ point to 26 -LRB- after reports that the movie and television production company was in takeover talks with <ORGANIZATION> Sony </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>. <ORGANIZATION> Paramount </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Communications </ORGANIZATION> was up 1 -RCB- to 56 -LCB-, <ORGANIZATION> IBM </ORGANIZATION> had gained 1 -LRB- to 117 -RRB- and <ORGANIZATION> General </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Motors </ORGANIZATION> was up 1 \ to 48 Meanwhile, <ORGANIZATION> Unisys </ORGANIZATION> was down \ to 19 |, <ORGANIZATION> Bethlehem </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Steel </ORGANIZATION> was off -RRB- to 21 and <ORGANIZATION> AMR </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> had lost -RRB- to 77 -LCB-
