<HEAD>London Shares Fall after Poor Trade Figures</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: UPDATES with close</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Shares fell sharply in moderate trading in <LOCATION> London </LOCATION> on Tuesday after publication of worse-than-expected trade figures for August. The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index, the most closely watched market index, finished 23.5 points, or 1.08 percent, lower at 2,336.1. The index finished just above its session low of 2,332.4 which followed news of the current account deficit last month of 1.99 billion pounds, or $ 3.20 billion, the third worst on record. A 1.5 billion pound, $ 2.4 billion, deficit had been expected. Volume came to 450.8 million shares, up from 280.5 million on Monday.
