<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Crude oil futures fluctuated throughout the day Tuesday before closing slightly higher as traders awaited the outcome of negotiations on <ORGANIZATION> OPEC </ORGANIZATION>'s production limits. `` It opened down on <ORGANIZATION> OPEC </ORGANIZATION> concerns and then it went up on <ORGANIZATION> OPEC </ORGANIZATION> concerns and bounced around during the day on different rumors,'' <PERSON> Jim </PERSON> <PERSON> Fiedler </PERSON>, an analyst with <ORGANIZATION> E.D. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> ; </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> F. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Man </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> International </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Futures </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, said of the crude oil market. The November contract for <ORGANIZATION> West </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Texas </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Intermediate </ORGANIZATION>, the benchmark grade of crude oil, finally closed 7 cents higher at $ 19.53 a 42-gallon barrel in <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Mercantile </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION> trading. In <LOCATION> Geneva </LOCATION>, ministers of the <ORGANIZATION> Organization </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Petroleum </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exporting </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Countries </ORGANIZATION> were trying to raise the cartel's production ceiling from its current 19.5 million barrel limit to a level between 20 million barrels a day and 21 million barrels for the rest of 1989 without sending prices skidding. The ministers twice postponed what was expected to be a final round of talks to consider a new Iranian proposal. Negotiations were to resume Wednesday after private bargaining sessions. Iranian Oil Minister <PERSON> Gholamreza </PERSON> <PERSON> Aqazadeh </PERSON> said his country had offered a plan to raise the production ceiling in the last quarter of the year. <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION> suggested hiking the cap to between 20.5 million barrels a day and 21 million barrels. The cartel has been overproducing, pumping more crude than allowed under an output agreement signed in June. Analysts' estimate <ORGANIZATION> OPEC </ORGANIZATION> production at about 22 million barrels daily Among refined products traded on the mercantile exchange Tuesday, heating oil for October delivery picked up 0.20 cent to settle at 57.71 cents a gallon. Unleaded gasoline for October delivery fell 1.29 cents to 60.38 cents a gallon amid reports of plentiful supplies.
